    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-16T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="8"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1–1648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macatee</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-16T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 16, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. Emile Ghory of <gloss target="#t_AHE1">AHE</gloss>, just returned from Cairo
                    meeting with Mufti, informed official ConGen following:</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>General national administration for whole Palestine will be established by
                        Arabs on day British terminate mandate. Administration now being organized
                        on basis Cairo press communique 5 January.</item>
                    <pb facs="0034" n="544" xml:id="pg_544"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Believes Abdullah<note n="1" xml:id="d8fn1">King of Transjordan.</note>
                        regardless private thoughts must accept Palestine Arab administration
                        although admits possibility various parts Palestine may be annexed to
                        bordering states. The line is that unimportant who takes over Palestine
                        provided Palestine remains Arab. Preference is for unified Palestine
                        state.</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Here follow Mr. Ghory’s further thoughts, including the observations that Arab
                    attacks on Jewish settlements were “for demonstration, training and probing
                    purposes” and that “Arms arriving increasing rate and young Arabs undergoing
                    rigid training.”]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macatee</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
